evaluation.response:
Sometimes the feeling of being alone can be overwhelming. No one wants to feel invisible. It hurts to feel like nobody would notice if something happened to you.

Feeling this way doesn't change your worth. You have inherent value, regardless of whether anyone knows what you're going through.&#x20;

If you ever need someone to talk to, there are resources available that can provide support and listening space. You don't have to face these thoughts alone, even if it feels like it. You deserve care, compassion, and understanding.
